        He used the index of coincidence, which measures the unevenness of the cipher letter frequencies. 
        By knowing the probability κp that any two randomly chosen source-language letters are the same (around 0.067 for monocase English) 
        and the probability of a coincidence for a uniform random selection from the alphabet κr (1/26 = 0.0385 for English), 
        the key length can be estimated as:
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>
