        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">
            where 
        N is the length of the text and n1 through nc  are the frequencies (as integers) of the "c" letters of the alphabet. 
        In our case the frequencies are supplied by the Frequency Test plug-in.
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">Let's see the plug-in in action
        </Span>
        <InlineUIContainer>
            <Image Source="/FriedmanTest;Component/DetailedDescription/Images/friedman1.jpg" />
        </InlineUIContainer>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Left" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333" />
    <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" TextAlignment="Center" FontFamily="Verdana" FontSize="13.3333333333333">
        <Span xml:lang="de-de">Just conect the plug-in as depicted in the screenshot above, or alternateively open
            the "Statistics-Test-Classical-02-be.cte" file, which is located in the Cryptool2.0 ProjectSamples folder. 
            It	should	be	noted	that	the	implemented	method	is	based	solely	on	Friedman’s	formula.	
            Therefore	the	plug-in	will	deliver a reasonably precise result only	under	certain	conditions.	
            Namely	–	input	should	be	taken	directly	from	the	Frequency	Test	plug-in	custom	Array	output	(black triangle output 
            on Frequency Test plug-in),	the	algorithm	settings	for	the	Frequency	Test	should	be	left	to	
            their	default	values	(Friedman’s formula is only valid for a 26 character alphabet).
        </Span>
    </Paragraph>

